The paper discusses improvements in the analysis of two classical algorithms for data structure maintenance, namely multipass pairing heaps and path-balanced binary search trees. These algorithms are commonly studied in the context of data structures, which falls under the category of "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS). The paper also involves the analysis of time complexity, which is a common topic in "Algorithms" (cs.AL). Additionally, the use of iterated logarithm functions suggests a connection to "Discrete Mathematics" (cs.DM) and "Information Theory" (cs.IT). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of lower bounds, which is a topic in "Computational Complexity" (cs.CC).
